# God's Eye — Atlas of Australia · environment variables
# Copy to .env and fill in the keys you want. Every layer degrades gracefully
# if its key is missing — the app works with zero keys, just with fewer layers.

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated list of origins allowed by the FastAPI CORS middleware.
# Default (when unset): http://localhost:8777,http://127.0.0.1:8777
# Add your deployed domain so the served HTML can fetch /proxy/* from itself:
#   GODS_EYE_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://gods-eye.onrender.com,http://localhost:8777
# GODS_EYE_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=

# Most container hosts (Render, Fly.io, Railway, Koyeb, etc.) inject PORT
# automatically. server.py honours it; falls back to 8777 for local dev.
# PORT=8777

# ── Google Maps (browser key — Directions, Places, POI overlay) ──
# Injected into gods-eye/index.html at serve time. Visible in DevTools to
# anyone who opens the page (unavoidable for Maps JS). Protected ONLY by
# HTTP referrer restrictions set in Google Cloud Console — NOT by secrecy.
# Set restrictions to:
#   http://localhost:8777/*, http://127.0.0.1:8777/*, https://YOUR-DEPLOY-URL/*
# Strongly recommended: set a $5/month billing budget alert in GCP.
# GOOGLE_MAPS_BROWSER_KEY=

# ── MapTiler (browser key — vector basemap) ─────────────────
# Free tier: 100k tile requests/month (hard cap, no surprise bill).
# Create at https://cloud.maptiler.com/account/keys/. Restrict by
# Allowed Origins: http://localhost:8777 + https://YOUR-DEPLOY-URL.
# Without this key the basemap won't render — recommended.
# MAPTILER_KEY=

# ── TomTom (browser key — live traffic flow tiles) ──────────
# Free Developer tier: 2,500 requests/day (hard cap, no surprise bill).
# Create at https://developer.tomtom.com/ → Dashboard → Apps.
# Restrict by Allowed Origins / HTTP Referrers as above.
# Optional — only used when the Traffic Flow overlay is toggled on.
# TOMTOM_KEY=

# ── TfNSW OpenData (server-side — incidents + live traffic cameras) ──
# Free, unlimited reads. Server-side only, never reaches the browser.
# Signup: https://opendata.transport.nsw.gov.au/ → My Apps → tick
# "Live Traffic — Hazards" + "Live Traffic — Cameras" when creating an app.
# Optional — without it, the Incidents and Cameras layers are empty.
# NSW_TRAFFIC_API_KEY=

# ── NSW FuelCheck (server-side — fuel prices) ───────────────
# Free, requires registration at https://api.nsw.gov.au/.
# Server-side only. Optional — fuel prices layer is empty without it.
# NSW_FUEL_API_KEY=
# NSW_FUEL_SECRET=
# NSW_FUEL_BASIC_AUTH=
